{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"319ae589-a10a-41f6-a56a-9bbfba2abf3f","content":"The issue is clear. In F#, **file compilation order matters** — files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but it's listed first in the `.fsproj`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_aioAn1G1oKJ04BgYhb2IH5","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-d6a18abb5eaf45288a17d403af93771d/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-d6a18abb5eaf45288a17d403af93771d/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"16a220e4-65a2-4433-a3a7-fe1aec7769b6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order in the `.fsproj` matters because F# uses a top-down compilation model - files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed before them.\n\nThe current order in the `.fsproj` is:\n1. `Services.fs` - which depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`)\n2. `Domain.fs` - defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` - depends on both\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs` - defines the base types\n2. `Services.fs` - depends on Domain\n\n\n3. `Program.fs` - depends on both\n\nNow I need to reorder the files in the `.fsproj` to fix this compilation issue.","outputTokens":465,"requestId":"1909:1C0D12:13AB701:1607102:6A066F01"},"id":"ff530474-d974-458b-a406-26c2dcb433b4","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:55:37.749Z","parentId":"dd8772bc-fe4d-42ac-951b-dc363489cecc"}
